ms on loy release was that the whole expansion sucked and charms were the only thing compelling people to go to loy. then you mix in that the charms were really modest and most considered it a waste of time.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=whizbangdustyboots>Whizbang Dustyboots</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elder Arcanist<BR>Gnomus Originalus</span><br>  Posts: 13469<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/22/03 7:20 pm)</font><br>     <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: alternate cod?..</span><hr size=1> Quin, stop being a jackass. You can solo everything on the ship in your low 50s. I'm not trying to justify a god damned thing, I was trying to be helpful. I had forgotten what a dumbass you are, though, so I'll hold off on trying to offer useful advice to you in future. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=acillatemzoso>Acillatem Zoso</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Channeler</span><br>  Posts: 238<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/22/03 8:49 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: alternate cod?..</span><hr size=1> Istari, <br>
<br>
the only key/flag I have is the Bangle of Disease Warding, and yes it gave me a Pop Progression Charm and 1 AA point.<br>
<br>
The camp is relatively easy with a tracker.  I've taken a group there and got all 4 drops in as little as 30 minutes (1 spawn rotation), and have seen it take as long as 4 hours.  Average time is about 2-3 hours to get all the pieces needed.<br>
<br>
Even at its longest (4 hours), that's not bad for 6 charms, and 6 AA points for a group of low-50s and if he's 49, this is probably his best (and only) option for getting the PoP progression charm.  Obviously he has other options for a charm, but I was just voicing one option easily doable with a group of players in his level range (he said he was 49).<br>
<br>
